Sure, here are several example sentences in Serbian that use the word "snima" in different forms and positions, along with their English translations:

1. On snima novu seriju za televiziju. (*snima*, present tense, third person singular) (He is filming a new TV series.)
2. Kamera će snimati ceo koncert. (*snimati*, future tense, third person singular) (The camera will record the entire concert.)
3. Već smo snimili tri epizode ove sezone. (*snimili*, past tense, first person plural) (We have already recorded three episodes this season.)
4. Da li si snimio taj film? (*snimio*, past tense, second person singular) (Did you record that movie?)
5. Ona će snimiti novi album uskoro. (*snimiti*, future tense, third person singular) (She will record a new album soon.)
6. Snimanje ovog filma trajalo je tri meseca. (*snimanje*, noun form) (The filming of this movie lasted for three months.)
7. Režiser je odgovoran za snimanje ovog filma. (*snimanje*, verb form used as a noun) (The director is responsible for the filming of this movie.)
8. Snimao je u svim vremenskim uslovima. (*snimao*, past tense, third person singular) (He recorded in all weather conditions.)
9. Moramo ponovo snimiti tu scenu. (*snimiti*, infinitive form) (We need to record that scene again.)
10. Snimljen je veliki broj filmova u tom studiju. (*snimljen*, past participle form used as an adjective) (A large number of movies were recorded in that studio.)

I hope this helps!